			 SETS


It is extention of tuple
It is used to store multiple items in a single variable
It is unordered, Unchangeable and unindexed
It is unchangeble but you can remove items and add new items(expand)
Here dublicates are not allowed
Boolean is same


SYNTAX:

1. Basic Syntax

city={"indore","dhar","ujjain","deas","jabalpur"}
print(city)


2. Duplicate values are not printing

city={"indore","dhar","ujjain","dewas","jabalpur","indore","ujjain"}
print(city)


3. Printing of boolean

city={"indore","dhar","ujjain","dewas","jabalpur","indore", True, False, 0}
print(city)

4. Finding the type 

city={"indore","dhar","ujjain","dewas","jabalpur",True, False, 0}
print(type(city))


5. Removing of duplicates from the list by using set

city=["indore","dhar","ujjain","dewas","jabalpur","indore"]
print("Before",city)
city2=set(city)				##list is convert to set
print("After:",city2)

6.  In And NOT In Operator 
	(to check wheather the element is present or not in the set)

city={"indore","dhar","ujjain","dewas","jabalpur","indore"}
print("indore" in city)
print("indore" not in city)
print("delhi" in city)



7. Add, Remove, DIscard method
	Add is used to add element
	Remove is uused to remove the element if not found it will error
	Disceard is same as remove but it will not give error if elemnt not found

student={"vedansh","aditya","mahak","tarun","rishi"}
print(student)
student.add("Kushagra")
print(student)
student.remove("tarun")
print(student)
student.discard("vimal")
print(student)


8. To update or extend the set

student={"vedansh","aditya","mahak","tarun","rishi"}
str=["pari", "priyanshi"]
student.update(str)
print(student)



student={"vedansh","aditya","mahak","tarun","rishi"}
student.update({"kush"},[2,5])
print(student)



9. Frozen set

	Used to create immutable version of set
	Here Adding and removing of elemnt are stoped

